  year = {1978},
  abstract = {Neonatal assessment is a structured procedure in which defined behaviors are observed and elicited. This process yields not only an objective description of the newborn's medical and behavioral status, but also a generalized affect upon the quality of the observer's subjective judgments. In the former and traditional way, the assessment procedure is used as a dependent variable. In the latter way, assessment is viewed as an independent variable or treatment of the adult (e.g., pediatrician, parent, child-care specialist). The value of structured behavioral assessment for teaching, primary medical care and research will be illustrated with examples from pediatrics, developmental and clinical psychology.},
