  abstract = {We previously reported psychophysical evidence for the exis- tence of a neural mechanism specifically sensitive to changin_£ object size. We now report that f~r narrow adapting stimuli, the changing- size specific threshold elevation is significant, providing the widths of the test and adapting stimuli do not differ by more than 0.5°. However, no significant elevation occurs for adapting stimuli wider than 1.5°. Further evidence that the changing-size channel is sensitive only to objects smaller than 1.5° is that aftereffects to changing size are explicable in terms of Waterfall effects at the moving edges when adapting stimuli are wider than 1.5°.},
