.05). It was lower in the PTZ treated mice (P< 0.05) than controls, but did not differ in the other groups of mice. The frequency of stretch attend postures (SAP) in the EPM test also differed between treatment groups (F(3,36) = 9.032; p< 0.001). SAPs were higher in the PTZ treated mice than in control (p< 0.001), DG and PTZ + DG treated mice (p< 0.01), but did not differ between control, DG and PTZ + DG treated mice. The number of head dips in the EPM also differed between the treatment groups (F(3,36) = 7.745; p< 0.001). PTZ treated mice did more head dips compared to controls (p< 0.05), DG alone (p< 0.01) and PTZ + DG treated mice (p< 0.01). The number of head dips were also lower in the PTZ + DG treated mice than control (p< 0.001). Percent time in the light in the LD test and the frequency of SAP did not dif},
  note = {QA: needs-split-review; booktitle inferred; Split from T44-split1-split2 at: 'T48)tPreliminary findings on the anti-ep'},
